Description: Flight into Egypt; the Virgin Mary holding the infant Christ and seated on a donkey being led towards right by an angel, with St Joseph at lower right facing left and holding a bundle over his shoulder, with cherubs in the air and trees to left; in a circular composition. c.1662 Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Stefano della Bella
Curator's comments: There are preparatory drawings for this etching in the Uffizi and the Ashmolean.
Additional IDs: Other BM number: X,5.4a (There is no X,5.4a in the 1837 register, and this must be the missing T,15.15 in the 1837 register.)
